In `Services/FileService.cs`, the private static `ComputeParent(string relative)` helper does manual `LastIndexOf('/')` and `Substring(0, separatorIndex)` operations to compute the parent of a forward-slash relative path. Rewrite it to delegate to `Path.GetDirectoryName(relative)` (the .NET runtime treats both `/` and `\` as directory separators on the supported targets; the input is already forward-slash so this is safe), then normalize the result back to forward slashes via `.Replace('\\', '/')`. PRESERVE THE EXACT CONTRACT, which differs from `Path.GetDirectoryName` in one case:
  - empty/null input → return `null` (Path.GetDirectoryName("") returns "" on Linux, so handle this case explicitly: `if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(relative)) return null;`)
  - single segment (e.g. "docs") → return "" (empty string) — Path.GetDirectoryName returns "" here, matches.
  - deeper path (e.g. "docs/reports") → return "docs" — Path.GetDirectoryName returns "docs", matches.
